199→     * PagedList tries to keep the visible item by adding new items outside of the screen while modifying the scroll
200→     * position. In most cases, this works out great because it doesn't interrupt to the user. However, after a new
201→     * item is inserted at the top while the list is showing the very first items, it feels very weird to not have the
202→     * inserted item shown. For example, if a new draft is added there is no indication of it except for the flash
203→     * of the scroll bar which is not noticeable unless user is paying attention to it.
204→     *
205→     * In these cases, we try to keep the scroll position the same instead of keeping the visible item the same by
206→     * first saving the state and re-applying it after the data updates are completed. Since `PagedListAdapter` uses
207→     * bg thread to calculate the changes, we need to post the change in the bg thread as well so that it'll be applied
208→     * after changes are reflected.
